@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p class="lead">
    FindActivity is an MVP for hosting and discovering local activities. This page describes what
    data we collect and how we use it. Replace this copy with your production policy before launch.
</p>

<h2>Information we collect</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Account data</strong> &mdash; email, display name, optional bio and birth date.</li>
    <li><strong>Activity data</strong> &mdash; activities you create or join, including title, description, location, and timing.</li>
    <li><strong>Reviews and ratings</strong> &mdash; reviews you leave for hosts after attending a completed activity.</li>
    <li><strong>Technical data</strong> &mdash; standard web-server logs (IP address, user agent, timestamps) for security and debugging.</li>
</ul>

<h2>How we use it</h2>
<p>
    We use your data to operate the service: showing activities near you, letting hosts and
    participants find each other, and preventing abuse. We do not sell your data. Location
    autocomplete and the map use the Mapbox Geocoding API &mdash; addresses you type may be
    sent to Mapbox under their terms.
</p>

<h2>Your choices</h2>
<p>
    You can edit or delete your account from the account management pages. To request a full
    export or deletion of your data, contact the site administrator.
</p>

<p class="text-muted">Last updated: @DateTime.UtcNow.ToString("yyyy-MM-dd")</p>
